CS_OFFLOAD_BETA1 by RedWood (released September 2009)

The setting of this map is a old railway unloading dock. The facility has been added to repeatedly over the years and it can be seen in the architecture of the structure. The CT's start off in the most modern section and make their way to the T side to rescue the hostages keep under the stairs and in the cargo container. There has a rather wide open but compact play area. If you control the second level you control the map so a good amount of your man power should be concentrate there. It should make for a fun and dynamic check point. Watch out for grenades and have fun.

About Playing with Bots: More or less playable NAV-file is included in archive.

This map far isn't ideal: a lot of empty and low-detailed spaces, some artefacts of the skybox and lightnings in some areas and something else.

But someone can be pleasant to play on it. And it has the right to receive the audience too, probably... :-)

Good Frags and Good Luck!

Finished after probably 30 compiles, after about two or three months. There are plenty of spawn points, but this map is not as big as it should be, so I would recommend a max of 6v6 gameplay.

911 was called discretely by a hostage from within the 4 story office building in the center of the city. The Swat Team has set up base in a garage across the street and are using it as a vantage point to launch a tactical strike on the office building. Terrorist hostiles have taken the building and are prepared to defend it to the death. Both have sent scouts out to the neutral building to the left of the office for a good vantage point.

Hey,
This is version 1 of Office Rescue by PowerThrust.

You are welcome to decompile the map, but please do not just retexture it
or copying obvious parts without crediting me!

I'm glad you chose to download this file, and its free for you to enjoy,
but if you are planning on using it on a server, please make a small donation to:

contact@3quarteraiming.com

Thanks :)

--------------------------------------

Install this by copying it to your:

Program Files/Steam/SteamApps/username/counterstike/cstrike/maps (or something similar) folder!

That should be it!

It supports 32 players (16 a side) although, occasionally the CT's may only be allowed 15.
This shouldn't matter because the map is intended for 12 players a team (and less).

It is a great little map and I hope you have fun playing it!

Thanks,
Moosey
(A.K.A. PowerThrust)

**Name:** cs_officelockdown

**Author:** ChiknWaflZ

**Description:** A very large Hostage Rescue map with three stories and lots of rooms! The idea was to make a map that would be a lot of fun with 10+ players and lots of team communication. There's tons of places for enemies to be hiding and you never know when one might jump out of nowhere and attack you! Be sure to move in groups and have plenty of fun!

**Instructions:** Extract the .zip file and copy the .bsp and .nav files into your Counter-Strike: Source map folder. This is usually under C:/Program Files/Steam/steamapps/(yourname)/counter-strike source/cstrike/maps. Enjoy!
